edu.ucla.sspace.vector
Class SparseHashVector<T extends Number>

java.lang.Object
  edu.ucla.sspace.vector.SparseHashVector<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
SparseVector<T>, Vector<T>, Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
SparseHashDoubleVector, SparseHashIntegerVector
public class SparseHashVector<T extends Number>
extends Object
implements SparseVector<T>, Serializable

A SparseVector implementation backed by a HashMap. This provides amoritized constant time access to all get and set operations, while using more space than the CompactSparseVector or AmortizedSparseVector classes.

See SparseHashArray for implementation details.

Author:
David Jurgens
